Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula will address Tuesday's precautionary grounding of aircraft by the Civil Aviation Authority. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. CAPE TOWN - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula will address Tuesday's precautionary grounding of aircraft by the Civil Aviation Authority. Hundreds of airline passengers were left high and dry following a scathing report about maintenance irregularities at Comair. READ: Some planes back in the air following grounding The CAA also grounded some British Airways and Kulula flights. The planes will only be allowed to leave the ground once the CAA deems them safe.